title: Jobless rate eases to 6.2 per cent
text:
Thu, Sep 10, 2015, 11:53 AM AEST - Australia Markets close in 4 hrs 7 mins Jobless rate eases to 6.2 per cent AAP – 8 minutes ago Print 
The jobless rate eased to 6.2 per cent in August, but Treasurer Joe Hockey warns employment data could be volatile in coming months. 
The decline in the unemployment rate from 6.3 per cent was expected by economists, but the number of people joining the workforce was stronger than forecast at 17,400. 
Before the figures were released on Thursday, Mr Hockey warned of some volatility in unemployment numbers because of increased workforce participation after a change to the government's jobs services program affecting about 40,000 Australians. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook $A rises after employment figures AAP
